AB = BA
\exp(A) \exp(B) = \exp(B) \exp(A)
\begin{align}\exp(A) \exp(B) &= (I + A + {\dfrac{1}{2}} A^2 + {\dfrac{1}{6}}A^3 + \ldots)(I + B + {\frac{1}{2}}B^2 + {\frac{1}{6}}B^3 + \ldots )\\ &= I + (A + B) + {\frac{1}{2}}(A^2 + 2AB + B^2) + {\frac{1}{6}}(A^3 + 3A^2 B + 3AB^2  +  B^3 ) + \ldots\\  &= I + (A + B) + {\frac{1}{2}}(A + B)^2 + {\frac{1}{6}}(A + B)^3 + \ldots \end{align}
