\exp(A)\exp(B) = \exp(A+B)
\exp(A+B) \equiv \sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{1}{n!}(A+B)^n.
A
B
\exp(A+B) = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{1}{n!}\sum_{m=0}^n\binom{n}{m}A^{n-m}B^m.
